  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      An investigation where patients with chronic heart failure and cheyne stokes respiration,
      treated with adapitve servo ventilator, will improve their cardiac function and quality of
      life.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Chronic heart failure (HF) is one of the most important public health problems in
      cardiovascular medicine.

      Several patients with chronic heart failure also has Cheyne Stokes respiration pattern.
      Earlier studies have shown that this respiration pattern improves with Adaptive servo
      ventilator. We wish to investigate wether this leads to improved cardiac function.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
